text:
I always appreciate you trying new things Gooruh, it inspires me to try new things too :_gurapat: I totally get why going online would be stressful for you; I find going online for the first time in a new game stressful anyway, and with the extra anonymity stress on top of that for you it's totally understandable. If you do feel comfortable and like you want to come back to this at some point when you are a little more familiar and feel like you can do it stress-free though, I'm always down for the journey of discovery with the best shork :_GuYum:Or, if you want to avoid some of that, maybe the rest of EN would be down for a sword-flailing tournament and getting medieval on eachother? Thank you for the fun stream as always, it makes me happy to be able to hang out with you üíô

Also, I'm sorry to hear that you're stressed out at the moment :_GuraCry: If my head feels like it's full of bees from stress, I find it useful to go somewhere away from all things which can distract me or demand my intention, then sit (feet flat on the floor, arms on the armrests) with my eyes closed and just pick up on things I can hear, smell, feel, whatever; like really actually give each thing my entire brain power. Then, when your noggin is whirring a little less, go through in your head exactly what you are gonna do for the rest of the day so your subconscious can partition off all the general stress/future tasks and just focus on today's stress. It isn't perfect, but sometimes it helps with the buzzing brain! Hope you can find a way that works for you sharkie :_gurapat:It's really nice to hear you talk about things you struggle with too (the eating anxiety for example). I have found so much common ground with you and other Holomems with struggles I have felt very alone with, and it is just very... I don't know, affirming(?) to hear that someone I respect and look up to has these problems too and it makes me feel less like I'm the only one ya know? Though of course I'm sad you have to suffer through these things :_GuraCry: If it helps to walk in to that field one step at a time, you could start with a member's fries comparison stream and work up from there if you wanted :)

P.S. Watched this wearing your birthday merch shirt for the first time; it's so comfy IKZ :_GuraAA:

text:
Wow, you picked a bad time to play Mordhau. The game is essentially dead and the small playerbase that remains is godawful. They've spent hundreds of hours mastering every single broken animation and unbalanced mechanic and do nothing but grief each other. God help you if you're a new/casual player. It's like Chivalry all over again, except the devs are somehow even worse.

If you want to play a medieval-style FPS, I'd recommend Vermintide 2. It's only horde-mode PvE but it's really fun, the learning curve is fairly easy, and randoms won't kick you from a match just because you accidentally got lost or don't know your role perfectly (that happened to me so many times in Deep Rock Galactic that I just gave up on the game).

text:
Sorry your day was stressful, Sharky. Mine was kinda bad too, but getting to spend time chatting with Gura and the Chumbiess made it better, so hopefully it helped you as well. Have fun getting some fancy new audio toys though; treat yourself to shiny things! And I know you talked about getting the schedule up soon (and you already told us what it would be yesterday) but you can always take a little time to recharge if you need it. If not though, and you'd rather chat with the Shrimps--you know where we'll be~

Also Goomba, whether what you like is Didney, Ponies, LARPing, or freakin Phineas and Ferb...like what you like, and be proud of it! You don't gotta explain nothin.

And lastly, to the idea of you trying to get over your eating anxiety on stream sometime: heck yeah, Sharky. I remember the days you'd go super hungry during stream cause you didn't want to eat on stream, and now here you are proposing something like that yourself. You've come so far, and I'm heckin proud of it. So let's get it!
